Text Notes 6550 3700 0    50   ~ 0
The adder gets constant input from the A and B registers, and 
Text Notes 6550 3800 0    50   ~ 0
constantly outputs its result to the line buffer chip (similarly to the 
Text Notes 6550 3900 0    50   ~ 0
registers), which only asserts to the data bus when the EO control 
Text Notes 6550 4000 0    50   ~ 0
signal is asserted. The actual adding is done by 2 74HC283 4-bit binary 
Text Notes 6550 4100 0    50   ~ 0
full adders, one of which outputs a carry bit to the other, allowing them to 
Text Notes 6550 4200 0    50   ~ 0
act as 1 8-bit adder.
